title: 9News Melbourne | Wednesday November 26 | Full Bulletin
description: Alicia Loxley and Tom Steinfort present the Melbourne news, covering the renewed police search for missing mother Samantha Murphy in Enfield State Park following new intelligence. We also bring you an update from the Supreme Court on the historic Easey Street murders case, where the accused has been committed to stand trial for two murder charges.  The biggest headlines include an inflation shock with prices rising faster than expected, fueling fears of a Christmas interest rate hike. In city news, the Metro Tunnel faces controversy over a potential pedestrian toll between stations, leading to a late government backflip. Plus, Victoria Police has been granted unprecedented powers to conduct random, warrantless searches across the CBD to combat knife crime, a move that has drawn strong criticism from civil liberties groups.  We also cover an Optus outage, a serious machete attack in Broadmeadows, an AFL Brownlow betting scandal update, and a look at the spectacular new Formula 1 Exhibition making its Australian debut in Melbourne. title: 9News Sydney | Wednesday November 26 | Full Bulletin
description: Peter Overton leads the bulletin with major news in Sydney, covering a day of extreme weather and significant national and international news. Sydney was unexpectedly hit by a severe summer storm, causing widespread damage, power outages, and commuter chaos, just as the state braced for catastrophic bushfire conditions in the regions.  Also in the bulletin: A shock rise in Australia's inflation figures puts pressure on the RBA for a potential rate hike, a tragic alleged murder in Rouse Hill leads to a second teenage arrest, and Robert Irwin dances his way to victory in the US 'Dancing with the Stars' competition.
